Aegis — Agentic AI Safety
=========================

Runtime AI agent safety net for Splunk + Cisco enterprises.

Version: 1.0.0
Author: Aegis Project
License: Apache-2.0

Supported Splunk versions: 9.4, 10.0, 10.1, 10.2, 10.3, 10.4
Supported platforms: Splunk Cloud, Splunk Enterprise

What this app does
------------------

Ingests Aegis verdicts (emitted via HTTP Event Collector by the aegis_mw
Python middleware) under the sourcetype cisco_ai_defense:aegis_verdict —
the same namespace populated by the Cisco Security Cloud Splunkbase app
(7404), so SOC analysts see Aegis events next to AI Defense events in
their existing search workflows.

Includes three Dashboard Studio v2 dashboards:

  - Agent Risk Overview — live counters, severity breakdown, blocked
    actions by agent
  - Verdict Inspector — drill-down on individual verdicts with full
    provenance (input text, evaluator chain, latency, OTel trace)
  - Regulator Evidence Pack — PDF-exportable view for examiners,
    with NIST AI RMF function alignment and SR 26-2 framing

Install
-------

Splunk Cloud:
  Apps -> Find more apps -> search "Aegis" -> Install
  (Or upload via Splunkbase once the app is published.)

Splunk Enterprise:
  $SPLUNK_HOME/bin/splunk install app /path/to/aegis_app.tgz
  $SPLUNK_HOME/bin/splunk restart

After install:
  Settings -> Apps -> Aegis -> Set up
  Configure the HEC token your aegis_mw middleware emits to so the
  cisco_ai_defense:aegis_verdict sourcetype is indexed.

